Place a symlink to the top-level cusp directory in current dir. Assuming
the top-level CUB directory is $CUSPDIR:

$ ln -s $CUSPDIR

program read mtx graph with the cusplibrary

and write colors of all vertices to "color.txt"

usage:
	./vc <graph>
	
Reference:

S. Dalton, N. Bell, L. Olson, and M. Garland, “Cusp:
Generic parallel algorithms for sparse matrix and graph
computations,” 2014, version 0.5.0.
http://cusplibrary.github.io/